{
  "stem": "4967.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the ghetto, when they [INAUDIBLE] the ghetto, we marched from the ghetto police yard to a [? sighting ?] in a subgroup of [INAUDIBLE], [?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Alexept ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were cattle trucks waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were loaded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we start moving at night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The train start moving at night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we travelled all night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the next morning, we arrive some German's cities or towns.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We saw the German flags and people walking around in Germany somewhere.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We got no food.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The train didn't stop.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after a few days, the train stopped.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the doors opened from the trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Those trains, cattle-- what do you call it-- cattle trucks, there are no windows, nothing, just a few openings on top to see through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Germans arrived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they say woman and children, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Women and children must leave the train, to disembark from the train.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Children went out of the train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My sister, bless her, went out of the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I and my brother, Chaim, were in the train facing not the door, but right in the back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the Germans came to every door of the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN] Everybody answered yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They're out.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They left the train.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They closed the doors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And a few hours later, we travelled for another two or three days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I can't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We travelled through German cities.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "You saw the German flags.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They were all actually Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] was in Poland.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We had no food supplies at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And it's unbelievable when I think back how we managed for a week to travel in filthy, dirty, smelly, stinking trucks of the trains.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There was no hygiene, no sanitation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "After three, or four, or five days, we arrived in Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
